Description: 1971 Gibson SG Standard in a super rare NATURAL finish. Large Guard, Lyher tailpiece, 60's appointments. Has the original black pat sticker T Top pickups. Covers have never been removed. Sodder has never been tapped on the pots and wiring harness. Excellent condition with a little wear and a few player dents (see photos). The pots read 13770. Natural finish was ONLY issued in 1971. I checked all cavities and it is not a refin. I listed this once before and had a few emails that suggested that this is a refin or stripped. NO sign of any other color ever on this guitar and all cavities show that this has always been a natural finish. All wear signs show that this is he original finish. Total mojo, you can feel every note and vibration through the entire guitar when playing. Includes a hardshell case, it's a little ruff on one end but secure. This is a really cool guitar, fun to play, amazing tone. Listing as an auction with a low starting point. I would keep it but I am down sizing. I have way too many guitars.
Title: Gibson SG Standard Rare Natural Finish 1971 1970 1969
